  "text": "Stack clash protection implementation in GCC is implemented across multiple key components:\n\n## Core Implementation Files:\n\n1. **gcc/explow.cc** (lines 1954-2200+): The generic stack allocation and probing implementation containing:\n   - `compute_stack_clash_protection_loop_data()` (line 1955): Computes loop data for dynamic stack allocation probes\n   - `emit_stack_clash_protection_probe_loop_start()` (line 2014): Emits the start of a stack probing loop\n   - `emit_stack_clash_protection_probe_loop_end()` (line 2036): Emits the end of a stack probing loop\n   - `anti_adjust_stack_and_probe_stack_clash()` (line 2072): Adjusts stack while probing to prevent stack clash attacks\n   - `anti_adjust_stack_and_probe()` (line 2201): Generic stack probing function for non-clash scenarios\n\n2. **gcc/explow.h**: Declarations for all stack clash protection functions and constants including `STACK_CLASH_PROTECTION_GUARD_SIZE`\n\n3. **gcc/common.opt** (line 3054-3057): Defines the `-fstack-clash-protection` flag:\n   ```\n   fstack-clash-protection\n   Common Var(flag_stack_clash_protection) Optimization\n   Insert code to probe each page of stack space as it is allocated to protect from stack-clash style attacks.\n   ```\n\n4. **gcc/params.opt** (lines 1108-1115): Defines the stack clash protection parameters:\n   - `-param=stack-clash-protection-guard-size`: Size of the stack guard (default 12, power of 2 in bytes)\n   - `-param=stack-clash-protection-probe-interval`: Interval for probes (default 12, power of 2 in bytes)\n\n## Target-Specific Implementation:\n\n5. **gcc/config/i386/i386.cc**: X86/X86-64 backend for stack clash implementation\n\n6. **gcc/config/i386/i386-protos.h** (lines 102-103): Declares the output functions:\n   - `output_adjust_stack_and_probe()`: Generates assembly for stack adjustment with probes\n   - `output_probe_stack_range()`: Generates assembly to probe a range of stack addresses\n\n7. **gcc/config/i386/i386.md** (lines 27820-27838): Machine description patterns for stack probing:\n   - `@adjust_stack_and_probe_<mode>` pattern (line 27815+): Emits probing code via `output_adjust_stack_and_probe()`\n   - `@probe_stack_range_<mode>` pattern (line 27830+): Emits range probing code via `output_probe_stack_range()`\n\n## Hook Definition:\n\n8. **gcc/target.def** (lines 6534-6545): Defines the `TARGET_STACK_CLASH_PROTECTION_ALLOCA_PROBE_RANGE` hook:\n   - Default implementation in `gcc/targhooks.cc` (line 2747): `default_stack_clash_protection_alloca_probe_range()`\n   - Declared in `gcc/targhooks.h` (line 305)\n\n## Support Infrastructure:\n\n9. **gcc/function.cc** (line 5679): `dump_stack_clash_frame_info()` - Diagnostic output for stack clash probing decisions\n\n10. **gcc/function.h** (lines 640-647): Defines `enum stack_clash_probes` with probe types and declares diagnostic functions\n\n11. **gcc/toplev.cc** (lines 1650-1662): Option validation for `-fstack-clash-protection`\n\n## Test Suite:\n\nMultiple test files in `gcc/testsuite/gcc.target/i386/` validate stack clash protection:\n- `stack-clash-protection.c`: Basic stack clash protection test\n- `stack-check-11.c` through `stack-check-19.c`: Various scenarios with different frame sizes and options\n- Tests verify correct probe generation with diagnostic output dumps\n\nThe implementation follows a two-level approach:\n1. **Generic level** (explow.cc): Core probing logic callable from any architecture\n2. **Target-specific level** (i386): X86/X86-64 code generation through output functions and machine description patterns"
}

